During Small Business Week, elected officials and business leaders are highlighting how tax reform and deregulation under President Trump are benefiting small businesses. They claim that small business optimism is at a record high, thanks to tax reform and other policy changes. They argue that the economy is back on track after years of slow growth and a stagnant economy, and small business owners are experiencing a favorable business environment. They also mention specific examples of small businesses benefiting from tax cuts, such as giving employees bonuses and being able to keep more of their own money. Overall, they argue that tax reform and deregulation have energized the economy and are driving record optimism and plans to expand among small businesses.